{
  "texts": [
    "The final tool we developed to support implementing DCTs in research workflows is an open source repository for psychological constructs: Psychological Construct Repository or PsyCoRe.",
    "We originally built this with the Hugo static site generator, leveraging its ability to integrate data from YAML files in a site to create a repository that can be hosted with minimal infrastructural dependencies (e.g.",
    "without requiring a database backend or a server-side parsed language).",
    "The Quarto ecosystem offers similar functionality, and has the added benefits of being simpler and quickly gaining popularity among researchers.",
    "The products generated by Hugo or Quarto (a set of static files) can be hosted using open source (and so open science-compatible) services such as Codeberg Pages or GitLab Pages, or even using closed source alternatives such as Netlify or GitHub Pages, for projects where applying open science principles is not desirable."
  ]
}